#DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS('maximum,minimum', 'increase,decrease', 'convex')
#  intervals of increase and decrease, convexity
#  of a cubic polynomial
#ENDDESCRIPTION

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = -$coef3 x^3 + $coef2 x^2 - $coef1 x + $coef0 \).
This function has two critical numbers \(A<B\)
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is increasing (type in INC) or decreasing (type in DEC).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, A] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [A,B] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [B,\infty) \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
BEGIN_TEXT
The critical number \(A\) is a relative \{ans_rule()\} (type in MAX or MIN)
and the critical number \(B\) is a relative \{ans_rule()\} (type in MAX or MIN)
END_TEXT
&ANS(std_str_cmp("MIN"));
&ANS(std_str_cmp("MAX"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
 \( f(x) \) has an inflection point at \( x =C \)
 $BR
where \( C \) is \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = ($a1+$b1)/2;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
Finally for each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is concave up (type in CU) or concave down (type in CD).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, C] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "CU";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [C,\infty) \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "CD";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
